# Hosts/links the link checker should NOT verify.
#
# The quality workflow's link check exists to catch OUR OWN broken local/relative
# links (e.g. an old `/game/` href that 404'd). It is deliberately NOT a monitor of
# the open internet: external sites go down, rate-limit, or block CI runners, and we
# don't want those flakes to fail a PR. The workflow also passes `--scheme file` so
# only on-disk links are even requested; this file is a second layer of safety in
# case absolute external URLs are ever scanned directly.

# Production / deploy domains (live state is out of scope for a PR check)
https://devbiz.kudbee.workers.dev
https://kudbee.com

# Common third-party hosts referenced from <head> (fonts, CDNs, schema, social)
https://fonts.googleapis.com
https://fonts.gstatic.com
https://schema.org
http://schema.org
https://www.w3.org
https://cdn.jsdelivr.net
https://unpkg.com

# Catch-all for any other absolute http(s) URL — external reachability is non-blocking.
^https?://
